        "label": "Organization API Key",
        "generateUrl": "https://docs.openreplay.com/en/api/",
        "setup": "In the OpenReplay app, go to **Preferences** → **Account** and copy the **Organization API Key**. The API docs state this key is used for all `v2` public API endpoints and is sent as `Authorization: Bearer {YOUR_ORGANIZATION_API_KEY}`. See [API overview](https://docs.openreplay.com/en/api/)."
      },
      "mcp_browser_login": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "OpenReplay MCP browser login token",
        "generateUrl": "https://docs.openreplay.com/en/mcp/setup",
        "setup": "Install the OpenReplay MCP app, point it at your OpenReplay instance, then ask the host to log in. The MCP returns an authorization link, you sign in to OpenReplay in the browser and click **Authorize**, then the host completes login and stores the issued token locally. See [MCP Setup](https://docs.openreplay.com/en/mcp/setup)."
      }
